sentences: Anuradha Paudwal (born 27 October 1954) is an Indian playback singer who works predominantly in Bollywood.
She has a long music career spanning over 4 decades.
She was awarded the Padma Shri, India's fourth-highest civilian award, by the Government of India in 2017.
She is ranked NO. 31 in Youtube's Music Charts and Insights list of top global artist as of 3 February 2022.
She has been on chart since last 237 weeks.
Anuradha made her debut from a Sanskrit verse in the 1973 Hindi film Abhiman, composed by S. D. Burman.
Early days and Success
She started her music journey in 1973 from film Abhiman.
In 1970s, she sang a few popular songs which were praised by the music composers as well as public.
She started her music journey from 1973.
In early 1990s, she gave one after one hit movies like Aashiqui, Dil Hai Ke Manta Nahin, Sadak, Dil, Beta, and Saajan.
Her singing talent was recognised by the audience for the first time for the Marathi film, Yashoda, released in the same year.
She has sung for about four decades through the soundtrack of movie songs, lyrics and hymns.
Dil Hai Ke Manta Nahin was 5th most selling soundtrack of 1991.
Sadak was the third most selling album of 1991.
On 12 September 2020, her son Aditya died of kidney failure.
1991: Best Female Playback Singer – "Nazar Ke Saamne" (Aashiqui)
1992: Best Female Playback Singer – "Dil Hai Ke Manta Nahin" (Dil Hai Ke Manta Nahin)
Best Female Playback Singer – "Tu Mera Hero Hain" (Hero (1983 film))
1991: Best Female Playback Singer – "Mujhe Neend Na Aaye" (Dil)
1992: Best Female Playback Singer – "Bahut Pyar Karte Hain " (Saajan)
1989:	Best Playback Singer (Female) – "He Ek Reshami" Kalat Nakalat (Marathi)
